"title": "7797: teaching",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "7797: teaching",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The apostles' teaching formed the basis of the instruction given to the first Christians. Parts of the NT draw a distinction between preaching and teaching, seeing the former as a means of converting individuals, and the latter as a means of instructing them after conversion.</p>\n<h2>The importance of teaching</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl12:11-Eccl12:12\">ECC 12:11–12:12</a></strong> <em>“goads” prod the sluggish to action, while “embedded nails” furnish a kind of mental anchorage. “Shepherd” is almost certainly a reference to God himself.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov1:8-Prov1:9\">PRO 1:8–1:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov3:1-Prov3:2\">PRO 3:1–3:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov4:1-Prov4:4\">PRO 4:1–4:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov6:20-Prov6:23\">PRO 6:20–6:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:19\">MAT 5:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor14:6\">1CO 14:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim4:2-2Tim4:3\">2TI 4:2–4:3</a></p>\n<h2>Teaching given by parents</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov22:6\">PRO 22:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut6:6-Deut6:9\">DEU 6:6–6:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut11:18-Deut11:19\">DEU 11:18–11:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph6:1-Eph6:4\">EPH 6:1–6:4</a></p>\n<h2>The apostles' teaching</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:42\">ACT 2:42</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus1:9\">TIT 1:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt28:19-Matt28:20\">MAT 28:19–28:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom6:17\">ROM 6:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom16:17\">ROM 16:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess4:8\">1TH 4:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Thess2:15\">2TH 2:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim1:10-1Tim1:11\">1TI 1:10–1:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim4:6\">1TI 4:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim6:3\">1TI 6:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim1:13-2Tim1:14\">2TI 1:13–1:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim4:3\">2TI 4:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus2:1\">TIT 2:1</a></p>\n<h2>The gift of teaching in the church</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom12:7\">ROM 12:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim4:13-1Tim4:14\">1TI 4:13–4:14</a></p>\n<h2>Ways of teaching believers</h2>\n<h3>Through example</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess1:5-1Thess1:6\">1TH 1:5–1:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor4:17\">1CO 4:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor11:1\">1CO 11:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil4:9\">PHP 4:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess2:14\">1TH 2:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim3:10\">2TI 3:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus2:3-Titus2:7\">TIT 2:3–2:7</a></p>\n<h3>Through dialogue with the teacher</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts20:7\">ACT 20:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts19:8-Acts19:9\">ACT 19:8–19:9</a></p>\n<h3>Through explanation of ceremonies</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod12:26-Exod12:27\">EXO 12:26–12:27</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod13:14-Exod13:16\">EXO 13:14–13:16</a></p>\n<h3>Through proverbs</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov1:1-Prov1:6\">PRO 1:1–1:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov1:20-Prov1:28\">PRO 1:20–1:28</a></p>\n<h3>Through the law</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut6:6-Deut6:9\">DEU 6:6–6:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut11:18-Deut11:19\">DEU 11:18–11:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut27:1-Deut27:26\">DEU 27:1–27:26</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps78:5-Ps78:8\">PSA 78:5–78:8</a></p>\n<h3>Through mutual edification</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col3:16\">COL 3:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom15:14\">ROM 15:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess5:11\">1TH 5:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb5:12\">HEB 5:12</a></p>\n<h3>Through the instruction of different groups within the church</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph5:22-Eph6:9\">EPH 5:22–6:9</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col3:18-Col4:1\">COL 3:18–4:1</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus2:1-Titus2:10\">TIT 2:1–2:10</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet2:18-1Pet3:7\">1PE 2:18–3:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet5:1-1Pet5:5\">1PE 5:1–5:5</a></p>\n<h2>The distinction between teaching and preaching</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts15:35\">ACT 15:35</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt4:23\">MAT 4:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt9:35\">MAT 9:35</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt11:1\">MAT 11:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke20:1\">LUK 20:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts4:2\">ACT 4:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts5:42\">ACT 5:42</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts28:31\">ACT 28:31</a></p>\n<h2>Examples of major themes taught in the NT church</h2>\n<h3>Righteousness from God through faith in Jesus Christ</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom3:21-Rom3:22\">ROM 3:21–3:22</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal2:20-Gal2:21\">GAL 2:20–2:21</a></p>\n<h3>Freedom in Christ from the demands of the law</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal5:1-Gal5:3\">GAL 5:1–5:3</a></strong></p>\n<h3>The humility of Jesus Christ</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil2:5-Phil2:8\">PHP 2:5–2:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb13:12-Heb13:13\">HEB 13:12–13:13</a></p>\n<h3>The supremacy of Jesus Christ</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col1:18\">COL 1:18</a></strong></p>\n<h3>The superiority of Jesus Christ</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb3:3\">HEB 3:3</a></strong> <em>Hebrews also shows Jesus Christ to be superior to the angels, the high priest and the sacrifices.</em></p>\n<h3>Godly behaviour</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph4:22-Eph4:24\">EPH 4:22–4:24</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom12:1-Rom12:2\">ROM 12:1–12:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim6:1-1Tim6:2\">1TI 6:1–6:2</a></p>",
